<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-04T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="558" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d558">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/369.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-04T11:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 2, 10 a.m. You may inform Theodore that an issue of paper
                            money at this time might compel the Department to cancel its offer
                            contained in first paragraph of its November 28, 8 p.m. Continue to keep
                            Department fully advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>